Garment Factory Fire Kills 9 in Bangladesh 
At least nine persons were burnt to death and five others injured when
a devastating fire gutted a garment factory Tuesday evening at Mirpur
area in the capital city of Dhaka, police sources said today.
Mirpur police said nine bodies were recovered today from inside the
garment factory while more bodies may remain under the debris.
The Rahman Garment is located at the fourth and fifth floors of a
six-storied building which caught fire at around 9 p.m. (local time)
Tuesday.
Fire service vehicles rushed to the spot and extinguished the fire at
midnight.
The cause of the fire could not be confirmed yet, police added.
